Job Description

We are looking for a talented and detail-oriented DevOps Engineer to support and enhance the infrastructure of our Data Engineering Team. This role is critical for ensuring the reliability, scalability, and efficiency of our data systems and pipelines. You will work alongside data engineers, software developers, and other stakeholders to build and maintain a robust development and deployment environment.

As a DevOps Engineer on the Data Engineering Team, you will be responsible for designing, implementing, and managing the CI/CD pipelines, infrastructure, and automation that enable seamless development and deployment of data engineering solutions. Your expertise in cloud platforms, system monitoring, and automation will help drive operational excellence and system reliability.

 

Responsibilities

-          Design, implement, and maintain scalable cloud infrastructure to support data engineering systems.

-          Build and optimize CI/CD pipelines for efficient deployment of data pipelines and services.

-          Automate routine tasks, including deployment, testing, and system monitoring, to improve efficiency and reduce manual effort.

-          Set up and maintain monitoring, alerting, and logging systems to ensure the reliability and performance of data solutions.

-          Implement and manage security best practices, including identity management, encryption, and secure access.

-          Work closely with data engineers, software developers, and QA professionals to ensure smooth integration and deployment of new features.

-          Identify and resolve infrastructure and deployment issues in a timely manner.

-          Maintain up-to-date documentation for systems, processes, and configurations.

-          Continuously evaluate and optimize system performance, scalability, and cost efficiency.

Position Requirements

-          5+ years of experience in a DevOps

-          Proven track record of managing and automating cloud-based infrastructure.

-          Hands-on experience with AWS (CloudFormation, EC2, S3, DynamoDB, â€¦)

-          Proficiency with Jenkins, GitLab CI/CD

-          Strong scripting skills in Python, Bash, or similar languages.

-          Excellent Docker knowledge

-          Familiarity with tools such as CloudWatch

-          Good Experience / Understanding in Pentaho

-          Good understanding of data warehouse systems like Snowflake, Redshift, and PostgreSQL.

-          Strong analytical and troubleshooting skills.

-          Ability to work effectively within a cross-functional team.
